WEBVTT

00:08.633 --> 00:09.842
Let me see what you got.

00:21.771 --> 00:23.898
Go. Go!

00:23.898 --> 00:25.733
Oh, my God.

00:25.733 --> 00:27.985
Oh, I heard you broke up
with your hot doctor lover.

00:27.985 --> 00:29.612
I heard you broke up
with yours.

00:29.612 --> 00:30.905
Yeah.

00:30.905 --> 00:31.739
Yeah, we're dumb.
So dumb.

00:31.739 --> 00:32.865
We're so dumb.

00:34.242 --> 00:35.827
Hey, where's
your baby?

00:35.827 --> 00:37.203
What?
I have a baby?

00:38.246 --> 00:40.164
She's ‐‐ She's having
a sleepover

00:40.164 --> 00:42.542
with my sister
in some fancy hotel.

00:42.542 --> 00:45.002
Which means that I can have
an adult sleepover.

00:45.002 --> 00:47.338
Oh. Hot.

00:47.338 --> 00:49.215
Hey, I think I love you.

00:51.384 --> 00:52.552
I can't hear you.

00:52.552 --> 00:54.262
Excuse me.

00:56.722 --> 00:59.976
So, are we talking about it
or drinking about it?

00:59.976 --> 01:01.227
The second thing.

01:05.355 --> 01:06.524
Oh, my God!

01:06.524 --> 01:08.776
My house!
My life!

01:08.776 --> 01:10.736
Don't worry.
My dad's coming.

01:10.736 --> 01:12.363
Right, Mami?
Sí, mi amor.

01:12.363 --> 01:13.948
They're coming.
They're coming.

01:17.326 --> 01:18.911
Move it, Souza.

01:20.538 --> 01:22.999
Look.

01:22.999 --> 01:24.834
Herrera,
charge that hose!

01:24.834 --> 01:26.085
Let's go, boys.

01:26.085 --> 01:27.628
Need that
delta wall opened up

01:27.628 --> 01:28.588
so I can check
for a connection.

01:31.591 --> 01:33.092
Phew.

01:33.092 --> 01:34.427
Have you at least
talked to him?

01:34.427 --> 01:36.262
Who, my husband?

01:36.262 --> 01:37.346
Or you mean the guy
who turned himself in

01:37.346 --> 01:38.598
to the Civil Service
Commission

01:38.598 --> 01:40.016
without consulting
his wife?

01:40.016 --> 01:41.851
Or, wait, do you mean the guy
who got suspended without pay

01:41.851 --> 01:43.186
for stealing narcotics

01:43.186 --> 01:44.896
in order to take down
our Fire Chief ‐‐

01:44.896 --> 01:46.189
which didn't work,
by the way ‐‐

01:46.189 --> 01:47.732
and all it did was
delay my father's funeral?

01:47.732 --> 01:49.025
You mean that guy?

01:49.025 --> 01:50.902
See, I'm confused
'cause...

01:50.902 --> 01:53.029
...I thought those were all
the same guy.

01:54.572 --> 01:55.656
Ugh.

01:56.866 --> 01:58.868
You know, I don't think
I've ever seen you

01:58.868 --> 02:00.995
not mad at your husband,

02:00.995 --> 02:03.080
which
is kind of funny

02:03.080 --> 02:04.290
'cause I don't think
I've ever seen you

02:04.290 --> 02:05.583
not mad at your dad,
either.

02:09.086 --> 02:11.380
Yeah.
No, not funny. Okay.

02:17.970 --> 02:19.722
 Ma'am, is there
anyone else in the house?

02:19.722 --> 02:21.891
No, no.
My husband's at work, thank God.

02:21.891 --> 02:24.685
Souza, help Herrera
knock that fire down!

02:24.685 --> 02:25.811
On it!

02:32.276 --> 02:34.320
Cap, looks like we've got
an electrical short.

02:34.320 --> 02:35.488
Well, you know
what to do.

02:35.488 --> 02:36.656
Copy.

02:36.656 --> 02:41.077
Andy. Your dad ‐‐
he's one of the greats.

02:41.077 --> 02:43.287
Thank you, ladies.

02:43.287 --> 02:44.956
Hi. It's Sandra.
Leave me a message.

02:46.541 --> 02:48.125
Hey.

02:48.125 --> 02:50.253
I don't want to talk
about my dad or my husband,

02:50.253 --> 02:52.046
so if it's either
of those things ‐‐
It's not.

02:54.882 --> 02:56.217
Okay,
it was gonna be,

02:56.217 --> 02:58.719
so now I'm just gonna stand here
in awkward silence.

02:58.719 --> 03:00.513
Come on. Come dance.

03:00.513 --> 03:02.974
We haven't all hung out
on our night off in forever.

03:02.974 --> 03:06.018
Okay, fine, but...

03:06.018 --> 03:07.270
I need another shot
first.

03:07.270 --> 03:09.647
Yes! Look who I convinced
to dance!

03:17.154 --> 03:19.991
Well, your old man did
pretty good today, m'ija, right?

03:19.991 --> 03:21.242
Mwah!

03:21.242 --> 03:22.577
 Let me take a picture
of the two of you.

03:22.577 --> 03:24.287
Of course. Okay.
Let's see.

03:24.287 --> 03:25.830
Look serious, like
a firefighter. Come on.

03:25.830 --> 03:27.164
One, two, and...
Beep!

03:27.164 --> 03:28.249
...three.

03:29.750 --> 03:31.419
Okay, back to work.
Mwah!

03:31.419 --> 03:32.545
Love you.

03:32.545 --> 03:34.588
Oh!
 Yes! Yes!

03:34.588 --> 03:35.756
That's awesome.
Whoo!

03:36.882 --> 03:38.426
Whoo!

04:04.076 --> 04:05.828
 Ugh.
Mnh.

04:05.828 --> 04:07.121
Wake up.

04:07.121 --> 04:08.456
We're getting
called in.

04:08.456 --> 04:09.582
Wait.

04:09.582 --> 04:10.833
Where's my phone?

04:13.669 --> 04:18.548
Ohh, fffffffor God's sake.

04:21.927 --> 04:23.095
What happened?

04:23.095 --> 04:24.597
Ahh! Why are you
in my bed?

04:24.597 --> 04:26.515
'Cause Travis and Emmett
slept in mine.

04:26.515 --> 04:29.393
Why are you yelling?
You can't just
sleep in my bed.

04:29.393 --> 04:31.479
Wait. Where's ‐‐
Where's my girlfriend?

04:31.479 --> 04:33.314
You have
a girlfriend?
Sasha!

04:33.314 --> 04:34.565
I wouldn't call her
your girlfriend.

04:34.565 --> 04:36.400
What?
Where is my girlfriend?!

04:36.400 --> 04:38.694
I don't know.
Why are you yelling?!

04:38.694 --> 04:40.988
My head hurts!
Aah! My head hurts, too!

04:40.988 --> 04:43.366
Guys, it is
a five‐alarm fire.
We got to go.

04:43.366 --> 04:45.576
No. No.

04:45.576 --> 04:47.119
No.
Ow. Ow!

04:47.119 --> 04:49.080
No! Stop.

04:49.080 --> 04:50.623
Did she sleep
in here?

04:51.916 --> 04:52.958
Emmett was
so smart to quit.

04:52.958 --> 04:54.377
Has anyone seen
my phone?

04:55.795 --> 04:57.004
That's it.
That's it.

04:57.004 --> 04:57.755
Is one of you
calling me?

04:57.755 --> 04:58.798
 Mnh‐mnh.

05:04.553 --> 05:06.597
No.

05:06.597 --> 05:09.266
No. Tía Sandra finally called me
back, and I missed it.

05:09.266 --> 05:10.893
Damn it!

05:10.893 --> 05:12.561
Uh, who's
Tía Sandra?

05:12.561 --> 05:13.729
Hey, you know what?

05:13.729 --> 05:15.856
It doesn't matter,
'cause we got to go!

05:15.856 --> 05:18.943
I'm supposed to have lunch
with Marsha, Inara, and Marcus.

05:18.943 --> 05:19.902
Change it
to dinner, Jack.

05:19.902 --> 05:21.779
Crap.
Robert's surgery.

05:21.779 --> 05:24.031
I'm supposed to be
at Grey‐Sloan, like, now.

05:24.031 --> 05:26.409
You know what?
You get a pass, okay?
You sit this one out.

05:26.409 --> 05:27.868
I love a good five‐alarm.

05:27.868 --> 05:29.286
Hey, don't worry.
There will be others.

05:29.286 --> 05:31.956
Go be with your...
battalion chief.

05:31.956 --> 05:34.583
Oh, my God, I still can't say
"husband," either.

05:34.583 --> 05:36.460
Hey, dude,
where's your girlfriend?

05:43.467 --> 05:44.719
Hey.

05:44.719 --> 05:46.011
Dad, what are
you doing here?

05:46.011 --> 05:47.304
Well, I figured
I'd stop by

05:47.304 --> 05:49.598
and see my daughter
the captain in action.

05:49.598 --> 05:51.100
I've been calling you
for days.

05:51.100 --> 05:52.852
I'm ‐‐ I'm ‐‐ I'm sorry.
There's been a lot going on.

05:52.852 --> 05:54.937
And I have to go, but just
hang here until I get back.

05:54.937 --> 05:57.565
Sure, kiddo.

05:57.565 --> 05:59.567
Hey.

05:59.567 --> 06:02.611
Go, Captain.

06:12.788 --> 06:14.665
What?

06:14.665 --> 06:16.292
I can just tell
from the way you smell

06:16.292 --> 06:18.127
that I am very glad
I had to stay home

06:18.127 --> 06:19.712
with two sick kids
last night.

06:19.712 --> 06:21.589
Yeah, you're so lucky.

06:24.091 --> 06:26.302
Tell me when we get there.
Will do.

06:28.137 --> 06:30.264
we've had an explosion
at Pac North.

06:30.264 --> 06:32.433
Contact Puget Sound Energy
to request a supervisor

06:32.433 --> 06:33.851
and gas‐leak response team.

06:33.851 --> 06:36.437
Additionally, we need Seattle PD
to shut down all traffic

06:36.437 --> 06:38.189
north and west of the hospital.

06:38.189 --> 06:39.607
 Thought the hospital
was closed.

06:40.649 --> 06:42.234
ER's open
and transferring admits.

06:42.234 --> 06:43.986
Radiology on the first floor,
research wing in the basement.

06:43.986 --> 06:45.154
Gas leak?
That's our guess.

06:45.154 --> 06:46.405
Utilities are off.

06:56.248 --> 06:57.750
Dispatch,
this is Pac North IC.

06:57.750 --> 06:59.084
We just had an explosion
on the third floor.

07:07.968 --> 07:10.095
 Seattle Fire!
Everyone needs to evacuate now!

07:10.095 --> 07:11.764
 Help!
Help, please!

07:11.764 --> 07:13.349
C‐Can someone help?!

07:13.349 --> 07:14.183
Hello?

07:14.183 --> 07:16.185
Hi! Yes!
I'm inside here!

07:16.185 --> 07:18.604
I have a bad back,
and I ‐‐ and I can't get out.

07:18.604 --> 07:20.231
There was an explosion
or something,

07:20.231 --> 07:23.359
and the kid just left,
ran out screaming.

07:23.359 --> 07:25.027
So I see they haven't improved
their staff much here.

07:25.027 --> 07:26.529
Alright,
we'll get you out.

07:27.738 --> 07:29.448
What‐‐ What's happening?

07:29.448 --> 07:31.575
It's jammed! I ‐‐
Machine must be faulty.

07:31.575 --> 07:33.077
Great hospital.

07:33.077 --> 07:34.828
And we can't use tools
because ‐‐

07:34.828 --> 07:36.121
Because this thing's
a giant magnet,

07:36.121 --> 07:37.456
and if it turns back on,
we're screwed.

07:37.456 --> 07:40.084
Oh, cool. That's just great
for my anxiety.

07:40.084 --> 07:41.085
Hey, buddy,
what's your name?

07:41.085 --> 07:42.461
Uh, Duncan.
Duncan.

07:42.461 --> 07:44.088
Okay, Duncan,
we're gonna get you out.

07:44.088 --> 07:47.424
How?
I weigh like 250.

07:47.424 --> 07:49.051
Well, that's okay,

07:49.051 --> 07:50.886
because our job
is to work out.

07:52.805 --> 07:54.223
It's not.
Okay.

07:56.559 --> 07:57.935
Seattle Fire!

08:00.437 --> 08:03.691
Everyone out!
Let's go! Let's go!

08:05.901 --> 08:08.279
Everyone, we need
to evacuate now!

08:08.279 --> 08:10.281
Monica, don't forget
the lab notes.

08:10.281 --> 08:11.949
And grab those samples
over there.

08:11.949 --> 08:12.741
 Ma'am,
did you hear me?

08:12.741 --> 08:14.410
Th‐There's a fire.

08:14.410 --> 08:16.412
I am not letting my life's work
burn to the ground.

08:16.412 --> 08:17.413
Lives depend on it.

08:17.413 --> 08:18.539
And it's not "ma'am."
It's "Doctor."

08:18.539 --> 08:20.165
 Really?

08:20.165 --> 08:22.543
Because your lives depend on us
evacuating you right now.

08:22.543 --> 08:24.044
This floor
is an active fire scene.

08:24.044 --> 08:25.462
Oh, damn it!

08:25.462 --> 08:26.964
Help me!

08:26.964 --> 08:28.966
Dr. Alba is really close
to a cure for lymphoma.

08:28.966 --> 08:30.759
You're firefighters.

08:30.759 --> 08:33.429
Your risk of developing
occupationally derived cancer

08:33.429 --> 08:34.679
is what?

08:36.097 --> 08:38.225
Grab all of those
frozen specimens in there.

08:39.602 --> 08:41.186
 Hey, uh, Duncan...

08:41.186 --> 08:43.022
...why were you
in the hospital today?

08:43.022 --> 08:44.523
Is it your back?
You rupture a disc?

08:46.984 --> 08:48.611
Hey, Duncan,
the more you talk,

08:48.611 --> 08:49.862
the less anxious you'll be.

08:49.862 --> 08:52.281
I cheated on my wife

08:52.281 --> 08:54.074
before we got married.

08:56.160 --> 08:58.329
Okay.
It was a mistake.

08:58.329 --> 09:00.581
It was just one night,

09:00.581 --> 09:03.959
and I've always,
always regretted it.

09:03.959 --> 09:06.128
But I can't never tell Carla.

09:06.128 --> 09:08.631
But I got to tell somebody,

09:08.631 --> 09:12.301
especially if I'm about to die.

09:14.678 --> 09:16.055
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

09:16.055 --> 09:18.098
Hey.
Hey, you know what?

09:18.098 --> 09:19.725
I slept with
an engaged friend.

09:19.725 --> 09:21.310
Yeah. I did.

09:21.310 --> 09:23.270
Even after
he wasn't engaged anymore,

09:23.270 --> 09:26.190
I kept sleeping with him
because I liked it.

09:26.190 --> 09:27.566
I slept with him
even after I knew

09:27.566 --> 09:29.109
he was falling in love
with me.

09:29.109 --> 09:30.986
I actually slept with him
last night.

09:30.986 --> 09:33.614
And a little bit
this morning.

09:33.614 --> 09:35.115
Do you love him?

09:37.660 --> 09:39.244
No.

09:39.244 --> 09:40.913
Th‐‐ That's cold.

09:40.913 --> 09:42.581
Yeah, I know.

09:47.628 --> 09:48.671
And, uh, you know ‐‐
And I ‐‐

09:48.671 --> 09:50.506
I‐I'm, uh ‐‐

09:50.506 --> 09:52.883
I am
extremely judgmental.

09:52.883 --> 09:54.259
What?
Yeah.

09:54.259 --> 09:55.636
You know, I'm a ‐‐
I'm a friendly guy.

09:55.636 --> 09:56.637
I like people.

09:56.637 --> 09:58.889
But, uh, I secretly
judge them

09:58.889 --> 10:00.307
for not living up
to my standards.

10:00.307 --> 10:02.267
You serious?
I am.

10:02.267 --> 10:04.895
I, uh, am silently judging you
right now.

10:04.895 --> 10:06.605
Both of you.

10:06.605 --> 10:08.148
 Hughes here.

10:08.148 --> 10:09.692
Requesting backup
in the research wing.

10:09.692 --> 10:11.986
Copy that.

10:11.986 --> 10:13.237
Warren and I
are on our way

10:13.237 --> 10:15.739
as soon as we evac
our patient.

10:29.461 --> 10:33.424
 Andy, your dad ‐‐
he's one of the greats.

10:46.186 --> 10:47.730
Robert, I'm so sorry
I'm late.

10:47.730 --> 10:48.856
You didn't come home
last night.

10:48.856 --> 10:50.107
I‐I told you.
What ‐‐

10:50.107 --> 10:51.525
I was ‐‐ I was hanging out
with the guys.

10:51.525 --> 10:53.068
You didn't tell me you were
sleeping over with the guys.

10:53.068 --> 10:54.069
You're right.
I'm sorry.

10:54.069 --> 10:55.529
I ‐‐ I'm ‐‐

10:55.529 --> 10:59.033
I'm still getting used to
this whole marriage thing.

10:59.033 --> 11:00.909
Sandra finally
called me back,

11:00.909 --> 11:03.412
but she didn't leave a message,
and now she's not answering,

11:03.412 --> 11:04.788
which is ‐‐ I mean,
she must know something, right?

11:04.788 --> 11:06.915
Maybe she heard about your
dad's passing and then tried to

11:06.915 --> 11:08.751
extend her condolences.
That's why she called.
She hated my father.

11:08.751 --> 11:11.045
She ‐‐ They didn't
speak for decades.

11:11.045 --> 11:12.421
He kept her from me.
He kept my cousins from me.

11:12.421 --> 11:13.922
You know,
sometimes it's easier

11:13.922 --> 11:15.799
to be mad at someone you lost
than to grieve them, Andy.

11:15.799 --> 11:17.634
I am grieving him.
You're trying to
find a reason...

11:17.634 --> 11:19.094
I‐I miss him...
...to be mad at
your father and ‐‐

11:19.094 --> 11:20.429
...every minute
of every day,

11:20.429 --> 11:22.848
and I'm furious with him
for lying to me

11:22.848 --> 11:23.932
and keeping my family
from me.

11:23.932 --> 11:25.059
Why can't both of
those things be true?

11:25.059 --> 11:27.394
Because he just died!

11:27.394 --> 11:29.396
Heroically.

11:29.396 --> 11:31.523
Saving your entire team.

11:31.523 --> 11:33.525
Okay.

11:33.525 --> 11:35.861
I'm
interrupting something, clearly.

11:35.861 --> 11:38.405
Dr. Shepherd, right?
Andy. Yeah.

11:38.405 --> 11:39.490
Good to see you again.
Good to see you.

11:42.785 --> 11:44.536
Hello?

11:45.704 --> 11:47.164
 Alright, everybody,
let's double‐time it.

11:47.164 --> 11:48.582
Come on.
Keep it moving, guys.

11:48.582 --> 11:49.750
Keep it moving.

11:49.750 --> 11:51.710
Double time.
Come on.

11:51.710 --> 11:54.379
Hey, Cutler, take them outside
and make sure they stay there.

11:54.379 --> 11:55.589
I don't want anyone else
coming back inside the building.

11:55.589 --> 11:56.924
Let's go.

11:56.924 --> 11:58.717
This incubator
and all these files ‐‐

11:58.717 --> 12:00.219
we need all of this out.

12:00.219 --> 12:01.261
 So, we're
a moving service now?

12:01.261 --> 12:02.971
Does she know
there's a fire upstairs?

12:02.971 --> 12:04.348
This is her
lymphoma research.

12:04.348 --> 12:05.557
She's refusing
to leave without it,

12:05.557 --> 12:06.850
and we can't leave
without her, so...

12:06.850 --> 12:08.352
Isn't all this stuff
digitized?

12:08.352 --> 12:10.604
You can't digitize
a living organism.

12:10.604 --> 12:11.939
I mean, she's right.
You can't.

12:11.939 --> 12:14.566
 Gibson, I need all of 19
out of that building now.

12:14.566 --> 12:15.734
Copy, Captain.

12:15.734 --> 12:17.277
Doctor, it's time
to go, okay?

12:17.277 --> 12:19.696
No! Get your hands
off of me!

12:20.989 --> 12:22.533
Look out!

12:23.909 --> 12:24.785
Ohh!

12:31.708 --> 12:32.584
Miller?

12:32.584 --> 12:34.336
Miller!

12:34.336 --> 12:36.672
Miller, you good?

12:36.672 --> 12:37.840
Everybody okay?

12:42.886 --> 12:44.847
Oh, no.
My God.

12:44.847 --> 12:46.932
 We have two firefighters
from 23 with blast injuries.

12:46.932 --> 12:49.101
19. 19, do you copy?

12:49.101 --> 12:50.477
Copy.

12:50.477 --> 12:52.980
Explosion above us caused
collapse of the hallway outside.

12:52.980 --> 12:54.398
Gibson here
with Hughes, Miller,

12:54.398 --> 12:56.108
Warren, Montgomery,
and one patient.

12:56.108 --> 12:57.901
But where's Dr. Alba?

12:57.901 --> 12:58.944
Dr. Alba?

12:58.944 --> 13:00.571
‐Doctor?!
‐Dr. Alba!

13:01.864 --> 13:03.448
 Come on.
Come on.

13:03.448 --> 13:05.159
Doctor, we're gonna
get you out, okay?

13:05.159 --> 13:06.451
My phone!

13:06.451 --> 13:09.037
I need my phone!
I need to call my partner!

13:09.037 --> 13:10.706
 Gibson,
do you have egress?

13:10.706 --> 13:11.874
Negative.

13:11.874 --> 13:14.626
Bishop. Sato. Report.

13:14.626 --> 13:16.628
Third explosion and fire
on the third floor

13:16.628 --> 13:18.797
weakened structural integrity,
causing partial collapse.

13:18.797 --> 13:20.549
We have two from 23 injured

13:20.549 --> 13:22.634
and five currently trapped
in the basement research wing.

13:22.634 --> 13:24.511
Chief! Chief Dixon!
Over here, sir!
Requesting USAR company
to come in

13:24.511 --> 13:26.138
a‐and...
Afternoon, all.

13:26.138 --> 13:27.389
Happy to answer any questions

13:27.389 --> 13:28.432
you may have at this time.

13:30.142 --> 13:31.518
What's USAR's ETA?

13:31.518 --> 13:33.520
He said
five minutes out.

13:36.481 --> 13:39.067
Anytime I say anything,
you think it's a criticism.

13:39.067 --> 13:41.111
You sound like it!
You're criticizing me!

