Well, guess what.
You deserve a break, baby.

21:00.592 --> 21:03.094
I want you to try
every single one of them, okay?

21:03.094 --> 21:06.473
I want you to experiment,
explore.

21:07.682 --> 21:10.644
Oh, yum!

21:10.644 --> 21:13.897
Promise me that you'll
never settle in life.

21:16.066 --> 21:18.109
There you go.

21:18.109 --> 21:20.070
Look at the sky, honey.

21:20.070 --> 21:21.446
Look at the sky.

21:21.446 --> 21:24.741
Never, ever take your eyes
off it.

21:24.741 --> 21:26.785
There we go. Whoo!

21:32.457 --> 21:34.668
Ohh!
Oh, my goodness!
Herrera!

21:34.668 --> 21:36.044
Oh. Are you okay?

21:36.044 --> 21:38.088
I'm ‐‐ I'm ‐‐
My husband's in surgery.

21:38.088 --> 21:39.381
I can get
an update for you.

21:39.381 --> 21:41.966
My dad died.
He ‐‐ He just died.

21:41.966 --> 21:44.219
I had heard that.
I'm ‐‐ I'm so sorry.

21:44.219 --> 21:45.637
I know the two of you
were close.

21:45.637 --> 21:46.971
I thought we were.

21:46.971 --> 21:49.474
Nothing makes sense
anymore.

21:49.474 --> 21:50.558
And, you know, every‐‐

21:50.558 --> 21:52.060
everyone thinks
it's the grief talking,

21:52.060 --> 21:54.145
and maybe it is, but I‐I can't
shake the feeling

21:54.145 --> 21:56.898
that maybe something
really awful happened.

21:56.898 --> 21:58.316
With your dad?

21:58.316 --> 22:00.110
With my mom.
Oh, God, I am sorry.

22:00.110 --> 22:01.111
You don't even know me.

22:01.111 --> 22:03.154
No, no. Listen.
It's okay.

22:03.154 --> 22:04.781
I‐I have plenty of stuff
in my own life.

22:04.781 --> 22:07.492
I could use a break.
You can talk.

22:07.492 --> 22:10.704
I thought my parents
were happy.

22:10.704 --> 22:15.417
But I‐I keep getting these
flashes of them fighting,

22:15.417 --> 22:17.669
screaming,
my mom crying.

22:20.380 --> 22:21.881
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

22:21.881 --> 22:23.508
I just ‐‐
It's okay.

22:23.508 --> 22:28.179
You know, the one favorite
memory I have of my mother,

22:28.179 --> 22:30.473
the one I‐I've kept with me
all these years,

22:30.473 --> 22:34.728
was our last fun day
together.

22:34.728 --> 22:36.438
And I‐I've always
held on to that

22:36.438 --> 22:38.440
as an example
of how much she loved me,

22:38.440 --> 22:40.859
how much I lost.

22:40.859 --> 22:42.902
But now ‐‐ now I think maybe

22:42.902 --> 22:47.282
she knew it was
our last day together.

22:47.282 --> 22:51.161
And now I think
maybe she killed herself.

22:53.413 --> 22:54.831
Oh, no.

22:56.249 --> 22:57.542
I'm sorry.

22:57.542 --> 22:59.961
It's okay.
It's okay.

23:06.009 --> 23:07.635
This is
the best day ever.

23:10.138 --> 23:12.474
I want you to remember
something, baby.

23:15.059 --> 23:17.562
If anything
ever happens to me,

23:17.562 --> 23:21.691
Daddy will always
take care of you, okay?

23:21.691 --> 23:24.652
What's gonna
happen to you?

23:24.652 --> 23:26.738
Nothing, honey.

23:26.738 --> 23:30.074
Just remember ‐‐
he'll take care of you,

23:30.074 --> 23:31.201
and you'll take
care of him, okay?

23:32.577 --> 23:34.370
I love you.

23:38.166 --> 23:40.251
and it's always been
just me and my dad.

23:40.251 --> 23:42.295
But I started to remember ‐‐

23:42.295 --> 23:44.881
